defaultA1.5 defaultThe scale of savings shown in these tests is significantly better than what is generally assumed, particularly for TRVs. The same house had an assessment carried out using the SAP methodology, which is the standard calculation tool used by Government in ma
defaultny of its policy tools such as the Green Deal. Under this tool the energy savings from the addition of TRVs is estimated at 2%, rather 
defaultthan the approximate 30% savings shown under the actual tests. On the basis of this new evidence Government should be doi
defaultng more to ensure that the full scope for demand reduction through the application of controls in all UK homes is realised in practice
default.
