default - What progress is the government making on reducing t
defaulthe demand for heat?
defaultA2.1 defaultIn terms of heat pumps progress has been very slow. Market growth in 2008/9 has flattened (less than 20,000 units per annum) with very little success in the one-off private market. This means the fourth carbon budget projections are unlikely to be met even
default with a successful RHI roll out unless a more focused strategic plan is deployed 
default(see A5 on Renewable Heat Zones)
default. 
